body:
@jerryshao  You are right, there is something wrong with python api when upload resource which have non-ascii-char name. Python api use `requests` to post file to livy server. File name is encoded by utf-8 if contails non-ascii-char. See detail: https://github.com/requests/requests/issues/2117
So, I add a function to decode file name after receive the http body in `InteractiveSessionServlet`.

I have tested java api and python api, the patch works well.
